Bola Bamigbola, Osogbo One Michael Adunola and a woman, Atinuke Olawoyin, on Tuesday appeared before an Osun State Magistrates’ Court sitting in Ile-Ife for killing two persons. They were accused of murdering Michael’s wife, Esther, and 14-month-old daughter, Glory. PUNCH Metro had reported that two headless bodies suspected to be a mother and her child were found in the Isale Agbara area of Ile-Ife. The police prosecutor, Sunday Osanyintuyi, said the accused committed the offences on May 23, 2020, around noon in Ile-Ife. He explained that Michael and Atinuke conspired and murdered the deceased. He said the accused unlawfully killed Esther and Glory, and severed their heads and hands. The offences, he stated, contravened sections 242, 319(1) and 516 of the Criminal Code, Laws of Osun State, 2002. Because of the nature of the case, the plea of the accused was not taken. Mr Adewale Adegbami and M. I. Babawale announced appearances for the accused. Magistrate Muhibah Olatunji asked the prosecutor to duplicate the case file and send a copy to the office of the Director of Public Prosecutions in the state for legal advice. She ordered that the accused be remanded in the Nigerian Correctional Centre, Ilesha, and adjourned the matter till July 28, 2020, for mention. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com